-- Hungarian March Wages Grow More Slowly as Public Salaries Drop
-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 2012-05-18T07:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-18/hungarian-march-wages-grow-more-slowly-as-public-salaries-drop.html
Hungarian  wages  rose less than
economists estimated in March as salaries for public employees
dropped from a year earlier.  The average monthly gross wage rose 2.7 percent from March
2011 to 222,741 forint ($941), the statistics office in Budapest
said in a statement today. The median estimate of 13 economists
in a Bloomberg survey was 6.5 percent.  Wage growth at private companies slowed to 5.8 percent in
March from 8.9 percent in February while salaries for public
employees dropped 4.5 percent in March after rising 2.1 percent
in the previous month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
